General
=======

We welcome all contributions. Please don't be afraid to submit an issue
if you would like a new feature, enhancement or if you find a bug.

If you would like to submit a pull request, please don't hesitate to do so.
It would be nice if you included any extra relevant documentation or unit
tests. It would also be nice if you were able to stick to PEP 8.

If there we feel that there is some discussion needed surrounding your
changes or request, please don't be discouraged we just wish to make this
libarary the best that it can be.

Cloning the Repository
----------------------

You can clone the repository with the following command:

.. code:: bash

    $ git clone https://github.com/Photonios/pyservice

You can install it in "editable" mode with the following commands:

.. code:: bash

    $ cd pyservice
    $ pip install -e .

By installing it that way, any changes you make to the source will be
reflected in the installed module immediately.

Branching
---------

If you wish to eventually submit a pull request, you will need to fork the
repository. This is most easily done in the github web ui which you can see
by visiting the following url in a browser
`https://github.com/Photonios/pyservice <https://github.com/Photonios/pyservice>`_

Look in the upper-righthand corner of the web page for the fork button.

Once forked, you can clone your own copy of the repository, create a branch
with the following command:

.. code:: bash

    $ git checkout -b my-feature-branch

Then in the github web ui, you can visit our repository and submit your pull
request.

Licensing
---------

This project is released under the GPL v2 and so your contributions if
made public must also carry the same license.

